# `include/` Header Map

This folder contains the shared public interfaces used by the ESP-IDF runtime.
Implementations live under `idf/main/`.

## Current Files

- `AppConfig.h`
  - Compile-time device/runtime constants (pins, panel geometry, touch calibration, defaults).
  - Consumed by display, touch, and app bootstrap paths.
- `RuntimeSettings.h`
  - Persisted user toggles/state loaded from NVS (12/24h, units, ADS-B radius).
  - Backed by `idf/main/RuntimeSettings.cpp`.
- `core/BootCommon.h`
  - Boot/runtime baseline logging helpers.
  - Backed by `idf/main/BootCommon.cpp`.
- `core/TimeSync.h`
  - NTP UTC sync helpers and UI time-context logging.
  - Backed by `idf/main/TimeSync.cpp`.
- `platform/Platform.h`
  - Generic platform primitives (time, logging, heap stats, Wi-Fi RSSI).
  - Backed by `idf/main/PlatformEspIdf.cpp`.
- `platform/Fs.h`
  - Filesystem abstraction (LittleFS begin/exists/mkdir/remove/rename).
  - Backed by `idf/main/FsEspIdf.cpp`.
- `platform/Net.h`
  - Network abstraction (connectivity, SSID/IP lookup, DNS resolve).
  - Backed by `idf/main/NetEspIdf.cpp`.
- `platform/Prefs.h`
  - NVS preference abstraction for typed get/put operations.
  - Backed by `idf/main/PrefsEspIdf.cpp`.

## Usage Guidance

- Put only stable cross-module interfaces in `include/`.
- Keep ESP-IDF-specific implementation details in `idf/main/*EspIdf.cpp`.
- Prefer adding new APIs to existing namespaces (`platform`, `boot`, `timesync`) before creating new top-level namespaces.
- When adding a new header:
  1. Add interface in `include/...`.
  2. Add implementation in `idf/main/...`.
  3. Include only what is needed (`<cstdint>`, `<string>`, etc.).
  4. Keep header dependencies minimal to avoid compile-time bloat.
